<subSubSection pageId="50" pageNumber="1389" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="50.[178,1085,516,686]" pageId="50" pageNumber="1389">
The group was established for two Japanese species (
<bibRefCitation author="LOBL I." box="[723,854,516,539]" journalOrPublisher="Revue suisse Zool" pageId="50" pageNumber="1389" pagination="727 - 799" part="77" refString="LOBL I. (1970 b): Revision der palaarktischen Arten der Gattungen Scaphisoma LEACH und Caryoscapha GANGLBAUER der Tribus Scaphisomini (Col. Scaphidiidae). - Revue suisse Zool. 77: 727 - 799." title="Revision der palaarktischen Arten der Gattungen Scaphisoma LEACH und Caryoscapha GANGLBAUER der Tribus Scaphisomini (Col. Scaphidiidae)" type="journal article" year="1970" yearSuffix="b">LÖBL 1970b</bibRefCitation>
). It includes at present a number of Asian species. They possess aedeagi with asymmetrical, narrow and elongate median lobe, usually have robust, prominent articular process and a small basal bulb. The parameres may be symmetrical or asymmetrical, usually lacking membranous lobes, and the internal sac is simple, consisting of a long flagellum, often to part extruded in repos.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
